Description: Fragment of sub-round, handle from neck join rising to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '341' and 441̣' Name Andrias. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roan Museum, MGR 054.08.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (25)
